It is estimated that R180 billion will be invested in energy infrastructure projects in South Africa over the next three years, while another R250 billion will be made available for investments in road and transport infrastructure.There is a clear investment opportunity for those who are able to capitalise on these investments.Moneyweb and financial services group Nedbank will be hosting a C-suite roundtable on November 30 2016, aimed at stimulating high-level discussions around the investment opportunities in the sector and how capital will be distributed. To register your interest in attending this event, please complete the form below: